{"title_page": "Geraldine James", "text_new": "{{short description|English actress}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}}\n{{Infobox person\n|image = \n|imagesize = 300px\n| name                    = Geraldine James\n| honorific_suffix        = [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] \n| birth_date              = {{birth date and age|1950|7|6|df=y}}\n| birth_place             = [[Maidenhead]], [[Berkshire]], England\n| death_date              =\n| death_place             =\n| occupation              = Actress\n| yearsactive             = 1973\u2013present\n| spouse                  = {{marriage|Joseph Blatchley|1986}}\n| children                = 1\n}}\n'''Geraldine James''', [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] (born 6 July 1950) is an English actress. Theatre director [[Peter Hall (director)|Peter Hall]] said that James ranks amongst the great English classical actresses.<ref>[http://www.bbc.co.uk/radio4/womanshour/2001_51_mon_01.ahtml \"Geraldine James\"] (17 December 2001) ''Woman's Hour'', Radio 4, BBC</ref>\n\nJames has been nominated four times for the [[British Academy Television Award for Best Actress|BAFTA TV Award for Best Actress]]; for ''Dummy'' (1977), ''[[The Jewel in the Crown (TV series)|The Jewel in the Crown]]'' (1984), ''[[Band of Gold (TV series)|Band of Gold]]'' (1995) and ''[[The Sins]]'' (2000). For her role as [[Portia (Merchant of Venice)|Portia]] in the 1989 [[Broadway (theatre)|Broadway]] revival of ''[[The Merchant of Venice]]'', she was nominated for the [[Tony Award for Best Actress in a Play]] and won the [[Drama Desk Award for Outstanding Actress in a Play]]. She also won the [[Volpi Cup for Best Actress]] at the 1989 [[Venice Film Festival]] for ''[[She's Been Away]]''. Her film credits include ''[[Gandhi (film)|Gandhi]]'' (1982), ''[[The Tall Guy]]'' (1989), ''[[Sherlock Holmes (2009 film)|Sherlock Holmes]]'' (2009), ''[[Alice in Wonderland (2010 film)|Alice in Wonderland]]'' (2010), ''[[The Girl with the Dragon Tattoo (2011 film)|The Girl with the Dragon Tattoo]]'' (2011), and ''[[45 Years]]'' (2015). Since 2017, she has starred in the [[Netflix]] series ''[[Anne (TV series)|Anne with an E]]'' as Marilla Cuthbert, and in the 2019 film ''[[Downton Abbey]]'' as Queen Mary.\n\n==Early life and family==\nJames was born in [[Maidenhead]], [[Berkshire]], to a [[cardiologist]] father.<ref>[http://www.filmreference.com/film/30/Geraldine-James.html Geraldine James Film Reference biography]</ref><ref>https://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/profiles/geraldine-james-a-talent-to-surprise-559204.html</ref> She was educated at [[Downe House School|Downe House]], a girls' independent school in [[Newbury, Berkshire|Newbury]], Berkshire. After graduating from the [[Drama Centre London]] in 1973, she began her career in [[repertory theatre]].\n\n==Credits==\n===Film appearances===\n*''The Dumb Waiter'' (1979) as Sally\n*''[[Bloody Kids]]'' (1980) as Ritchie's Wife\n*''[[Sweet William (film)|Sweet William]]'' (1980) as Pamela\n*''[[Gandhi (film)|Gandhi]]'' (1982) as [[Mirabehn]]\n*''[[The Tall Guy]]'' (1989) as Carmen\n*''[[The Wolves of Willoughby Chase (film)|The Wolves of Willoughby Chase]]'' (1989) as Mrs. Gertrude Brisket\n*''[[Prince of Shadows]]'' (1991) as Rebecca Osorio\n*''[[If Looks Could Kill (film)|If Looks Could Kill \u2013 Teen Agent]]'', (1991) as Vendetta Galante\n*''[[The Bridge (1992 film)|The Bridge]]'' (1992) as Mrs Todd\n*''[[Words Upon the Window Pane]]'' (1994) as Mrs. Henderson\n*''[[Moll Flanders (1996 film)|Moll Flanders]]'' (1996) as Edna\n*''[[The Man Who Knew Too Little]]'' (1997) as Dr.  Ludmilla Kropotkin\n*''[[Lover's Prayer]]'' (2001) as Mother\n*''[[An Angel for May]]'' (2002)\n*''[[Calendar Girls]]'' (2003) as Marie\n*''[[Northanger Abbey (2007 film)|Northanger Abbey]]'' (2007) as the narrator\n*''[[Sherlock Holmes (2009 film)|Sherlock Holmes]]'' (2009) as [[Minor Sherlock Holmes characters#Mrs. Hudson|Mrs Hudson]]\n*''[[Alice in Wonderland (2010 film)|Alice in Wonderland]]'' (2010) as Lady Ascot\n*''[[Made in Dagenham]]'' (2010) as Connie\n*''[[The Girl with the Dragon Tattoo (2011 film)|The Girl with the Dragon Tattoo]]'' (2011) as Cecilia Vanger\n*''[[Arthur (2011 film)|Arthur]]'' (2011) as Vivienne Bach\n*''[[Sherlock Holmes: A Game of Shadows]]'' (2011) as [[Minor Sherlock Holmes characters#Mrs. Hudson|Mrs Hudson]]\n*''[[45 Years]]'' (2015) as Lena\n*''[[Alice Through the Looking Glass (2016 film)|Alice Through the Looking Glass]]'' (2016) as Lady Ascot\n*''[[Rogue One]]'' (2016) as Jaldine Gerams (Blue 3)\n*''[[Daphne (film)|Daphne]]'' (2017)\n*''[[Megan Leavey]] '' (2017) as The Veterinarian\n*''[[Beast (2017 film)|Beast]]'' (2017)\n*''[[Downton Abbey (film)|Downton Abbey]]'' (2019)<ref>[https://variety.com/2018/film/news/imelda-staunton-geraldine-james-downton-abbey-movie-1202922680/ Imelda Staunton, Geraldine James Join 'Downton Abbey' Movie]</ref> as [[Mary of Teck]]\n\n===Music appearances===\n*''[[Human. :II: Nature.]]'' (2020)\n\n===Radio appearances===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Date !! Title !! Role !! Director !! Station\n|-\n| {{dts|format=dmy|2000-02-21}} \u2013 {{dts|format=dmy|2000-03-03}} || ''[[Gaynor Macfarlane#The Hours|The Hours]]'' ||  || [[Gaynor Macfarlane]] || [[BBC Radio 4]] [[Woman's Hour Drama]]\n|- \n| {{dts|format=dmy|2003-03-21}} \n| ''[[Baldi (radio)|Baldi]]: The Book Case'' \n| Maggie\n| Mark Lambert \n| BBC Radio 4 [[Afternoon Play]] \n|-\n| {{dts|format=dmy|2003-04-19}} || ''[[Gaynor Macfarlane#Turtle Diary|Turtle Diary]]'' || Neaera || Gaynor Macfarlane || BBC Radio 4 [[Saturday Play]]\n|-\n| {{dts|format=y|2005}} || ''[[Jeremy Mortimer#The Raj Quartet|The Raj Quartet]]'' || Mildred Layton || Jeremy Mortimer || BBC Radio 4\n|}\n\n===Television appearances===\n*''[[The Sweeney]]: Pay Off''  (1976)  as Shirley Glass\n*''Dummy'' (1977) as Sandra X\n* ''[[The History Man]]'' (1980) as Barbara Kirk\n*''I Remember Nelson'' (1981) as Emma Hamilton\n* ''[[The Jewel in the Crown (TV series)|The Jewel in